The knowledge graph has disconnected subgraphs that need to be connected.

RELATIONSHIP ONTOLOGY — use ONLY these types:
{% for r in relationship_ontology_rich %}
  Type       : {{ r.type }}
  Description: {{ r.description }}
  From       : {{ r.from | join(" or ") }}  →  To: {{ r.to | join(" or ") }}
  Attributes : {{ r.attributes | tojson }}
{% endfor %}

MAIN GRAPH ENTITIES (the large connected component — connect the isolated entities to these):
{{ main_entities | tojson(indent=2) }}

ISOLATED ENTITIES (the small disconnected subgraph — find connections from these to the main graph):
{{ isolated_entities | tojson(indent=2) }}

DOCUMENT TEXT (use this as evidence for any relationships you find):
{{ document_text }}

TASK:
Find all relationships that connect the ISOLATED ENTITIES to the MAIN GRAPH ENTITIES.
There must be at least one relationship. Look carefully — the connection may be indirect
or expressed through shared attributes (same person, same organisation, same account, etc.).

For EACH relationship type the required output structure is:
{% for r in relationship_ontology_rich %}
{{ r.type }}:
  {
    "type": "{{ r.type }}",
    "source": "<id of a {{ r.from | join(' or ') }} entity>",
    "target": "<id of a {{ r.to | join(' or ') }} entity>",
    "attributes": {
      "evidence": "<verbatim or paraphrased quote from document>",
      {% if r.attributes is mapping %}{% for attr in r.attributes.keys() %}"{{ attr }}": "<value or null>"{% if not loop.last %},
      {% endif %}{% endfor %}{% endif %}

    }
  }
{% endfor %}

Return:
{
  "relationships": [ ... all relationships connecting isolated entities to main graph entities ... ],
  "reasoning": "<brief explanation of how these subgraphs are connected>"
}

Rules:
- source and target must be IDs that exist in either the main or isolated entity lists above.
- At least one endpoint of each relationship must be in the isolated entities list.
- At least one endpoint of each relationship must be in the main graph entities list.
- Use ONLY ontology-defined relationship types.
- "evidence" is REQUIRED on every relationship.
